RIFT VALLEY FEVER - YEMEN
*************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Rift Valley fever - Saudi Arabia 20000917.1592
Rift Valley fever - Saudi Arabia: WHO confirmation 20000919.1612
[1
Date: 20 Sep 2000
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: News media

At least 50 people have died in the poor Arab state of Yemen in the last 2
days from the viral disease Rift Valley Fever, which is spread to humans
from livestock, a government official said on Wednesday.
The official told [news reporters that the deaths took place in northern
Yemen close to the border with Saudi Arabia, where at least 16 people have
also died from Rift Valley Fever.
"Initial reports show the death of more than 50 people, most of them in
Wadi Moor in Huseidah region," said the Yemeni official, who refused to be
identified.
He said that several families had lost more than one member to the disease.
*******
[2
Date: Wed, 20 Sep 2000 22:45:29 +0200
From: Matias SACLA <msacla@zahav.net.il>
Source: Europa Press, 20 Sep 2000 [in Spanish
<http://es.news.yahoo.com/000920/4/jpei.html>
Via: ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org>

This report which was published in Spanish indicates that the death toll
due to Rift Valley fever has risen to 77 persons in Yemen.
